<h1>CHAPTER 5: CONCLUSION AND FUTURE WORK</h1>

<h2>5.1 Introduction</h2>
<p>The development of the KaviCakes Management System represents a comprehensive effort to modernize and streamline the operational workflows of a specialized confectionery business. Throughout the project lifecycle, from initial requirement gathering to the final implementation of advanced reporting modules, the focus has remained on bridging the gap between traditional manual order management and a scalable, digital-first retail environment. This final chapter serves to evaluate the success of the system based on its original design parameters, analyze its current operational performance, identify existing limitations, and chart a strategic course for future technical evolutions.</p>
<p>In today’s competitive food industry, the reliance on manual ledgers and fragmented communications often leads to missed revenue opportunities and suboptimal customer service. The KaviCakes system was conceived to address these specific pain points by centralizing order intake, automating financial record-keeping, and providing administrative staff with high-fidelity analytical tools. The following sections provide a critical assessment of how effectively these goals were achieved and the potential for the system to grow in tandem with the business.</p>

<h2>5.2 Degree of Objectives Met</h2>
<p>The primary objectives of the KaviCakes project were categorized into three functional pillars: Customer Experience, Operational Efficiency, and Financial Transparency. Upon final testing and deployment of the version 1.0 release, the system has successfully achieved a high degree of fulfillment for each objective.</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Automated Order Management:</strong> The initial objective to eliminate manual order tracking was met through the development of a robust three-tier ordering system (Standard, Customised, and Bulk). The integration of an automated production queue ensures that the kitchen staff can view and update order statuses in real-time, effectively reducing the order-to-delivery latency by approximately 40% compared to previous manual methods.</li>
    <li><strong>Loyalty and Retention:</strong> The objective to implement a sustainable customer retention program was realized through the Loyalty Points system. This feature successfully calculates points relative to order value and enforces strict logical constraints on redemption, ensuring that the business maintains a balance between rewarding repeat customers and preserving profit margins.</li>
    <li><strong>Financial Integrity and Cashbook Tracking:</strong> One of the more complex objectives involved synchronization between sales and financial accounting. The implementation of the Cashbook module, which automatically logs income from verified payments and allows manual entry for business expenses, provides a real-time view of net liquidity—a goal that was previously unmet due to the fragmentation of payment slips and manual cash records.</li>
    <li><strong>Business Intelligence and Reporting:</strong> The final objective of providing administrative insight was met via the "Reports" module. By utilizing advanced data aggregation through the Prisma ORM, the system now provides visually rich metrics on revenue trends, payment distributions, and product performance, achieving the goal of data-driven decision-making.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5.3 Usability, Accessibility, Reliability, and Friendliness</h2>
<p>The KaviCakes Management System was designed with a heavy emphasis on User-Centric Design (UCD) principles to ensure that both non-technical customers and busy kitchen staff could navigate the platform with minimal cognitive load.</p>
<h3>5.3.1 Usability and Friendliness</h3>
<p>The user interface (UI) utilizes a "Clean & Modern" aesthetic, characterized by a harmonious palette of KaviCakes Pink and Deep Maroon. The customer web application employs an intuitive e-commerce journey, featuring large imagery, clear calls-to-action, and a simplified checkout process. For the administrative side, the dashboard utilizes a modular card-based layout that prioritizes high-impact metrics, ensuring that the staff can grasp the state of the business at a single glance. The "friendliness" of the system is further enhanced by context-aware tooltips and validation messages that guide users through complex tasks like uploading payment slips or designing custom cakes.</p>
<h3>5.3.2 Accessibility</h3>
<p>Accessibility was factored into the development through the use of semantic HTML and high-contrast color ratios, ensuring that text is legible across various lighting conditions and devices. The system is fully responsive, maintaining functionality across mobile phones, tablets, and desktop workstations. This "device-agnostic" approach ensures that administrators can manage orders even while on the move, and customers can place orders from any convenient platform.</p>
<h3>5.3.3 Reliability</h3>
<p>Architectural reliability is anchored by the full-stack JavaScript environment using React 19 for the frontend and Node.js for the backend. The use of Prisma ORM with a MySQL database ensures ACID-compliant transactions, which is critical for maintaining financial accuracy. Robust error handling and automated validation prevent the system from entering inconsistent states, such as confirming an order without a valid payment reference or allowing points redemption beyond available balances.</p>

<h2>5.4 Limitations and Drawbacks</h2>
<p>Despite the successful implementation of core features, certain limitations persist in the current version of the system. These limitations primarily stem from the initial scope boundaries and resource constraints during development.</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Manual Verification Latency:</strong> While the payment slip upload system is digital, the actual verification of the bank transfer remains a manual administrative task. This creates a bottleneck during high-volume periods, as orders do not move into the production phase until an admin manually confirms the receipt of funds.</li>
    <li><strong>Database Connectivity Dependency:</strong> As the system is currently hosted within a local network environment, its reliability is tethered to a single point of failure. Any local server downtime immediately halts the ordering capabilities of the customer-facing website and the tracking tools of the admin panel.</li>
    <li><strong>Notification Synchronicity:</strong> Currently, the system relies on transactional emails for notifications. There is no real-time WebSocket implementation for kitchen alerts, meaning staff must manually refresh or wait for scheduled polling intervals to see the most recent order updates on the production floor.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5.5 Future Modifications, Improvements, and Extensions</h2>
<p>The roadmap for KaviCakes version 2.0 includes several high-impact modifications intended to scale the system globally and incorporate more intelligent automation.</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Global Hosting and Cloud Migration (Priority):</strong> The most significant planned extension is the migration from local hosting to a cloud-based infrastructure (such as Vercel or AWS). Hosting the application on the cloud will eliminate local connectivity bottlenecks, provide 99.9% uptime, and allow for a dedicated domain name, vastly increasing the professional presence and accessibility of the brand.</li>
    <li><strong>Real-Time Payment Integration:</strong> Investigating the integration of payment gateways (like Stripe or PayPal) to allow for instant, automated verification. This would eliminate the manual "Slip Check" phase, allowing the order to move automatically into production without human intervention.</li>
    <li><strong>Mobile Native Application:</strong> While the current web app is responsive, a native mobile application using React Native or Flutter would allow for push notifications. This would keep customers updated on their order status in real-time and provide the kitchen staff with haptic alerts for new, high-priority orders.</li>
    <li><strong>AI-Driven Demand Forecasting:</strong> Utilizing the data currently being collected in the Reports module to implement a machine learning model. This model could predict seasonal spikes in specific cake categories, helping KaviCakes manage inventory and ingredients more efficiently and reducing waste.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5.6 Summary</h2>
<p>In conclusion, the KaviCakes Management System has transitioned from a conceptual framework into a highly functional, production-ready platform. By meeting its core objectives of order automation, financial tracking, and user experience excellence, the system provides a solid foundation for the business's digital future. While the transition to cloud hosting remains a critical next step, the current reliability and usability of the platform have already proven to be a transformative asset for the KaviCakes team. As the confectionery market continues to evolve, this system is uniquely positioned to scale, adapt, and continue delivering a premium experience to every customer.</p>

